Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing, @cider vinegar{30%ml}, @wholegrain mustard{17%g} and some @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and mix into the dressing.

== Charred Corn ==

Drain the @sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once charred, transfer the corn to the bowl of tomatoes. Set the pan aside.

== Peri Peri Chicken ==

Sprinkle the @Peri Peri seasoning{2%sachet} over a large #plate{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Lay one of the @British chicken thighs{4} in the spice, then turn to coat both sides evenly. Continue with the other thigh(s).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan and fry until browned on each side and cooked through and slightly charred, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, thinly slice the chicken.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and sweet potato to the bowl of corn and tomatoes. Toss together so everything's coated in the dressing.

Share the salad between your #serving bowls{} and lay the chicken on top. Dollop on some @soured cream{75%g} and finish with a sprinkle of the @pumpkin seeds{15%g}.

Enjoy!